# Loop frontend — copy to .env and fill in.
#
# ONLY VITE_-prefixed vars are exposed to the browser bundle. Never put a
# server secret here (no DB URL, no JWT secret, and NEVER the embeddings/LLM
# key — those live in backend/.env only). Anything in here ships to the client.

# In dev, API calls go to /api and Vite proxies them to the backend (see
# vite.config.js), so leave this UNSET for local development. For a deployed
# build where the API is on another origin, set it in `.env.production` (Vite
# loads that only on `vite build`, never in `npm run dev`) or in the host's
# build-time env — NOT in `.env`, which also loads in dev and would make
# `npm run dev` bypass the proxy. No trailing slash.
# .env.production:  VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-api.onrender.com

# Google Maps JS key (Sprint 2 EventDetail map) — a browser-restricted,
# public-by-design key. Lock it to your domains in the Google console.
# VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_KEY=

# Google Sign-In — OAuth 2.0 Web client id (the SAME value the backend verifies
# against as GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID). Public-by-design, not a secret. When unset, the
# "Continue with Google" button is hidden and email auth is the only path. The
# client's Authorized JavaScript origins must include your dev origin
# (http://localhost:5173) and, later, the deployed frontend origin.
# VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
